Fix apps/web/postcss.config.js — it's using ES module syntax which breaks Next.js.

Replace the entire file content with CommonJS format:

module.exports = {
  plugins: {
    tailwindcss: {},
    autoprefixer: {},
  },
}

Do NOT use "export default". PostCSS config must use module.exports.

Then run: pnpm build (from apps/web directory) and show me the output.

Create apps/web/src/app/global-error.tsx with exactly this content, 
saved as UTF-8 without BOM:

'use client';

export default function GlobalError({
  error,
  reset,
}: {
  error: Error & { digest?: string };
  reset: () => void;
}) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        <div>
          <h2>Something went wrong</h2>
          <button onClick={reset}>Try again</button>
        </div>
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}

Then check if the file was created:
Get-Content apps/web/src/app/global-error.tsx

Then also check apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx for any non-ASCII characters 
or encoding issues — run:
[System.IO.File]::ReadAllBytes('apps/web/src/app/layout.tsx') | 
  Select-Object -First 3

If the first 3 bytes are 239, 187, 191 that means it has a BOM (byte order mark)
which can cause issues. If so, rewrite the file without BOM.

Finally:
Remove-Item -Recurse -Force apps/web/.next
pnpm --filter @artifact-hub/web dev
